+# File Explorer v0/shadcn Source Contract - 2026-06-09
+
+Target repo: `trugurpala/pala-os-v5`
+
+Target feature: file explorer UI shell
+
+Phase: v0/shadcn source contract
+
+Status: `PARTIAL`
+
+Release posture: not release approval
+
+## Current Decision
+
+The file explorer is still not implemented in v5.
+
+This contract records the exact v0.dev/shadcn prompt, data boundary, import boundary, validation plan, and rollback path required before generated UI output can enter the repo as product code.
+
+Decision: `READY_FOR_V0_OUTPUT`
+
+Missing evidence before implementation import:
+
+- actual v0.dev output URL, component id, generated archive, or GitHub branch
+- generated file list
+- UI render evidence
+- responsive evidence
+- owner review or explicit approval to import generated code
+
+## Product Scope
+
+The first file explorer pass is a read-only UI shell.
+
+It may include:
+
+- desktop-window style app frame
+- left navigation tree
+- breadcrumbs
+- search input
+- file list with folder/file rows
+- preview/details panel
+- selection state
+- empty state
+- loading skeleton state
+- error/manual-verification state
+- settings entry point
+- responsive layout for desktop, tablet, and mobile
+
+It must not include:
+
+- real filesystem mutation
+- delete, rename, move, upload, download, or write operations
+- reading private local files
+- reading `.env`, secrets, runtime DBs, ledger payloads, or customer data
+- external service writes
+- release, deploy, tag, or public readiness claim
+- dashboard success state unless backed by evidence records
+
+## Data Boundary
+
+First pass data mode: `MOCK_ONLY_READ_ONLY`
+
+The generated UI may use local in-memory mock rows only.
+
+Approved mock schema:
+
+```ts
+type FileExplorerItem = {
+  id: string
+  name: string
+  kind: "folder" | "file"
+  extension?: string
+  sizeLabel: string
+  modifiedLabel: string
+  ownerLabel: string
+  status: "synced" | "local" | "locked" | "needs-review"
+  path: string
+}
+```
+
+Approved mock roots:
+
+```text
+/Desktop
+/Documents
+/Projects
+/Evidence
+```
+
+These roots are product labels only. They must not read the real local filesystem in the first pass.
+
+## Exact v0.dev Prompt
+
+Use this prompt in v0.dev when generating the first implementation candidate:
+
+```text
+Create a production-quality Pala OS file explorer UI shell using React, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, and shadcn/ui primitives.
+
+Context:
+- Pala OS is a local-first control tower and OS-like workspace.
+- Agent does the work. Pala OS verifies the work.
+- The first pass must be read-only and mock-data only.
+- Do not access the real filesystem.
+- Do not show fake success. Empty, loading, error, and manual-verification states must be explicit.
+
+Visual direction:
+- OS desktop window inside a serious local control tower.
+- Avoid generic SaaS dashboard cards.
+- Use a compact, high-signal interface with strong information hierarchy.
+- Prefer neutral/zinc/slate tokens, one cyan/teal command accent, and quiet status badges.
+- Use shadcn/ui primitives where appropriate: Button, Card, Badge, Input, ScrollArea, Table, DropdownMenu, Sheet, Separator, Skeleton, Tabs or Breadcrumb.
+- Use lucide-react icons consistently at 16-20px.
+
+Layout:
+- Header: breadcrumbs, search, view toggle, refresh/mock-sync button, settings button.
+- Left rail: roots tree for Desktop, Documents, Projects, Evidence.
+- Main pane: file/folder rows with name, kind, size, modified date, owner, status, and row actions.
+- Right pane: selected item details, path, status, mock metadata, and disabled dangerous actions.
+- Bottom strip: read-only boundary notice and evidence requirement.
+- Mobile: collapse left tree and details panel into sheets; keep search and list usable at 360px width.
+
+States:
+- default populated mock state
+- empty folder state
+- loading skeleton state
+- manual verification required state
+- selected file/folder state
+
+Accessibility:
+- Keyboard reachable controls.
+- Clear labels for search, navigation, row actions, and details.
+- No color-only status indicators.
+
+Important restrictions:
+- No real filesystem APIs.
+- No upload/download/delete/rename/move behavior.
+- No secrets, credentials, or runtime DB data.
+- No "production ready", "all systems green", or fake PASS claims.
+
+Output:
+- Provide a self-contained React component named PalaFileExplorer.
+- Include mock data in the same file unless you create a separate mock-data file.
+- Include a short integration note listing all generated files and dependencies.
+- Include a rollback note.
+```
+
+## Generated Output Intake Contract
+
+When v0 output exists, record the source before import:
+
+| Field | Required value |
+| --- | --- |
+| v0 source | URL, component id, generated archive, or GitHub branch |
+| generated files | exact paths and source refs |
+| dependencies | exact package names and versions if new dependencies are needed |
+| data mode | must remain `MOCK_ONLY_READ_ONLY` unless a separate court approves read/write |
+| validation evidence | UI render, responsive check, and repo command output |
+| rollback | commit hash or file list removable by normal git revert |
+
+## Expected Import Paths
+
+Because v5 does not yet have an approved Next.js product app scaffold, generated output must not be wired into a fake production route by default.
+
+Allowed first intake locations:
+
+- `docs/v0/file-explorer/<date>/` for raw generated output archive notes
+- `docs/migration-court/` for court notes
+- a future product app path only after the Next.js app scaffold decision exists
+
+If the owner explicitly approves an interim static control preview, add it under:
+
+```text
+control/file-explorer/
+```
+
+with status labels that say `Manual verification required` or `Mock UI only`, never `PASS`.
+
+## Validation Plan
+
+Validation required after generated output is imported:
+
+```powershell
+npm.cmd run pala:source-audit
+```
+
+If product UI code is added, also capture:
+
+- desktop render evidence
+- mobile responsive evidence at 360px width
+- source diff review for fake success language
+- confirmation that no filesystem write APIs were introduced
+
+No validation was run for this contract-only phase.
+
+## Rollback Note
+
+Rollback this contract-only phase with:
+
+```powershell
+git revert <commit-containing-this-file>
+```
+
+Rollback of a later generated UI import must be recorded separately with its exact commit and file list.
+
+## Court Result
+
+Status remains `PARTIAL`.
+
+The next safe action is to run the prompt in v0.dev or provide a Figma node-specific URL, then import the generated output only after recording its source reference.
